  "notes": "Sampling; cost = numel(output).",
  "notes_sections": [
    "The variable obtained by summing the squares of `df` independent, standard normally distributed random variables:",
    ".. math:: Q = \\sum_{i=1}^{\\mathtt{df}} X^2_i",
    "is chi-square distributed, denoted",
    ".. math:: Q \\sim \\chi^2_k.",
    "The probability density function of the chi-squared distribution is",
    ".. math:: p(x) = \\frac{(1/2)^{k/2}}{\\Gamma(k/2)} x^{k/2 - 1} e^{-x/2},",
    "where :math:`\\Gamma` is the gamma function,",
    ".. math:: \\Gamma(x) = \\int_0^{-\\infty} t^{x - 1} e^{-t} dt."
  ],
  "numpy_ref": "np.random.chisquare",
  "parameters": [
    {
      "body": [
        "Number of degrees of freedom, must be > 0."
      ],
      "name": "df",
      "type": "float or array_like of floats"
    },
    {
      "body": [
        "Output shape.  If the given shape is, e.g., ``(m, n, k)``, then",
        "``m * n * k`` samples are drawn.  If size is ``None`` (default),",
        "a single value is returned if ``df`` is a scalar.  Otherwise,",
        "``fnp.array(df).size`` samples are drawn."
      ],
      "name": "size",
      "type": "int or tuple of ints, optional"
    }
  ],
